<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=5880&amp;p=54539#p54539"><![CDATA[
Some people reject Aerith for the same reason it's called Tetris, not Tetrith. But then Babel Fish has translated "Tetorisu" (Japanese name for Tetris) as "Tet lith", where "Tet" is the first day of the Vietnamese lunar year.<br /><br />Speaking of Tetris and game versions, the rare Tetris for Game Boy (version 1.0) had a <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=PknsQwSD46M" class="postlink">very different music 1</a>, not the <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=zXeCEzaNLKM" class="postlink">Korobeiniki</a> of the much more common Tetris for Game Boy (version 1.1) that has become The Tetris Company's <a href="http://tarr.uspto.gov/servlet/tarr?regser=serial&amp;entry=77037539" class="postlink">trademark</a> tune (despite <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=fgcYU9WRfTY#t=0m18s" class="postlink">Happy-hopper</a>).<br /><br /><em>tepples snaps out of it and realizes he isn't posting on Hard Drop Forums</em><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Tue Dec 29, 2009 5:24 pm</p><hr />
